# UJL Clean Code: Architecture Boundaries

## Goal

Keep package responsibilities and dependency direction explicit.

## Must

- Respect layer direction: `types` -> `core` -> `ui` -> `adapter-*` -> `crafter`.
- Keep validation and schema ownership in `types`.
- Keep composition/AST concerns in `core`.
- Keep editor-specific behavior in `crafter`.
- Call out public API changes and keep backward compatibility unless explicitly breaking.

## Should

- Prefer additive type changes over destructive interface changes.
- Reuse shared primitives instead of cross-layer shortcuts.

## Avoid

- Importing higher-layer implementation into lower layers.
- Hiding cross-package coupling behind utility modules.
- Moving package-specific behavior into generic layers for convenience.

## Allowed Exceptions

- Build-time toolchain integration explicitly documented in architecture docs.
- Transitional adapters during planned migrations with clear removal path.
